==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr}} ''[[abjuratio]]'': compare {{etyl|la}} ''abjuration''.

===Pronunciation===
*: {{rhymes|eɪʃǝn}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The act of [[abjuring]] or [[forswearing]]; a [[renunciation]] upon oath; as, ''abjuration'' of the [[realm]], a [[sworn]] [[banishment]], an oath taken to leave the country and never to return.
# A solemn [[recantation]] or [[renunciation]]; as, an '''abjuration''' of [[heresy]].

====Derived terms====
* '''Oath of abjuration''', an oath [[asserting]] the right of the present royal family to the crown of England, and [[expressly]] abjuring [[allegiance]] to the [[descendants]] of the [[w:Jacobitism|Pretender]] - [[Brande & C]]

